%% Sequence Diagram — User Onboarding Journey (9-Step Wizard)
%% Next-Gen Observability Onboarding Platform

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant User as App Team User
    participant UI as Frontend SPA
    participant API as Backend API
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    participant CE as Capacity Engine
    participant GE as Governance Engine
    participant Grafana as Grafana MCP
    participant Jira as Jira MCP
    participant Confluence as Confluence MCP
    participant ServiceNow as ServiceNow MCP

    Note over User,ServiceNow: Step 1 — Application Identity

    User->>UI: Enter app name, app code, portfolio
    UI->>API: GET /api/v1/lookup/portfolios
    API->>DB: Query application_metadata
    DB-->>API: Portfolio list
    API-->>UI: Portfolio options
    UI->>API: POST /api/v1/onboarding (draft)
    API->>DB: INSERT onboarding_requests (status=draft)
    DB-->>API: Created request with UUID
    API-->>UI: { id, status: "draft" }

    Note over User,ServiceNow: Step 2 — Technical Profile

    User->>UI: Select hosting platform, tech stack
    UI->>API: PUT /api/v1/onboarding/{id}
    API->>DB: UPDATE hosting_platform, tech_stack
    API-->>UI: Updated request

    Note over User,ServiceNow: Step 3 — Telemetry Signal Selection

    User->>UI: Toggle Metrics, Logs, Traces, Profiles
    User->>UI: Configure per-signal details
    UI->>API: PUT /api/v1/onboarding/{id}
    API->>DB: UPSERT telemetry_scopes
    API-->>UI: Updated request with telemetry_scope

    Note over User,ServiceNow: Step 4 — Environment Matrix

    User->>UI: Select environments per signal (dev, qa, staging, prod)
    UI->>API: PUT /api/v1/onboarding/{id}
    API->>DB: UPSERT environment_readiness rows
    API-->>UI: Updated request

    Note over User,ServiceNow: Step 5 — Capacity Check

    UI->>API: POST /api/v1/capacity/check
    API->>Grafana: Query current usage per signal (MCP)
    Grafana-->>API: Usage data (series, MB/s, spans/sec)
    API->>CE: Evaluate capacity (thresholds + projections)
    CE-->>API: CapacityCheckResponse (GREEN/AMBER/RED)
    API->>DB: INSERT capacity_assessments
    API-->>UI: { overall_status, signal_results[], recommendations[] }
    UI->>User: Display capacity traffic lights

    alt RED — Capacity Blocked
        UI->>User: Show block message with escalation link
    else AMBER — Proceed with Monitoring
        UI->>User: Show warnings, allow continuation
    else GREEN — All Clear
        UI->>User: Show green status, proceed
    end

    Note over User,ServiceNow: Step 6 — Similarity Search

    UI->>API: POST /api/v1/similarity/search
    API->>DB: Vector similarity query (pgvector)
    DB-->>API: Top-K matched applications
    API->>DB: INSERT similarity_matches
    API-->>UI: { matches[]: { app, score, exporters, dashboards, alerts } }
    UI->>User: Display matched apps with reusable artifacts

    Note over User,ServiceNow: Step 7 — Governance Validation

    UI->>API: POST /api/v1/governance/validate
    API->>GE: Run all HARD + SOFT rules
    GE-->>API: GovernanceResult { passed, score, violations[] }
    API-->>UI: { passed, score, hard_violations[], soft_violations[] }

    alt HARD Violation Detected
        UI->>User: Block submission, show violations + suggestions
    else SOFT Violations Only
        UI->>User: Show warnings, allow override
    else All Rules Pass
        UI->>User: Show green governance score
    end

    Note over User,ServiceNow: Step 8 — Artifact Preview & Generation

    UI->>API: POST /api/v1/artifacts/preview
    API-->>UI: Preview of CR, Epic, Stories, Tasks
    User->>UI: Review and approve artifacts
    UI->>API: POST /api/v1/artifacts/generate
    API->>DB: INSERT artifacts (status=draft)
    API->>Jira: Create Epic + Stories (MCP)
    Jira-->>API: External IDs + URLs
    API->>ServiceNow: Create CTASKs (MCP)
    ServiceNow-->>API: External IDs + URLs
    API->>Confluence: Create runbook page (MCP)
    Confluence-->>API: Page URL
    API->>DB: UPDATE artifacts (status=synced, external_id, external_url)
    API-->>UI: { artifacts[]: { type, external_id, external_url } }

    Note over User,ServiceNow: Step 9 — Review & Submit

    UI->>User: Display full summary of onboarding request
    User->>UI: Click Submit
    UI->>API: PUT /api/v1/onboarding/{id} (status=submitted)
    API->>DB: UPDATE status=submitted, submitted_at=now()
    API->>DB: INSERT audit_logs (action=submitted)
    API-->>UI: { status: "submitted" }
    UI->>User: Confirmation with tracking links
